1. Hong Kong Treasury Director: The law does not rule out the possibility of stablecoins being pegged to the RMB, and a comprehensive assessment of risks and policy coordination is required;
2. Thailand SEC publicly solicits opinions on the listing standards for digital asset exchange tokens, and plans to relax restrictions on the listing of related party tokens;
3. QCP: The implied volatility structure of BTC and ETH releases downward expectations, and the market is waiting for key catalysts;
4. Telegram ecological trading application Blum has opened airdrop inquiries: 30% can be received on the day of TGE, and the remaining part will be unlocked in equal amounts in 180 days;
5. Sahara AI: Jointly with OKX, an exclusive airdrop event of 28 million tokens will be launched, divided into 2 major reward pools;
6. Mexico's third richest man has increased his Bitcoin holdings again, and BTC-related assets account for more than 70% of his investment portfolio;
7. Norwegian company K33 received 185 million Swedish kronor in funds, which will be used to increase Bitcoin reserves;
8. GMGN launched the iOS APP version "GMGN - Meme Track".
